# Intuition
Whenever the array is sorted and we have to find an element, the answer is Binary Search. But the more beautiful thing is, you can just observe how our Brains solved this problem: Pick up an element and eliminate the other part of search Space. Exactly what Binary Search Does.

Pick the middle element of the search space and eliminate the other half.

# Approach
1.Set left to 0 and right to the last index of the letters array.
2. Repeat the following steps while left is less than or equal to right:
	a.Calculate the middle index mid as the average of left and right.
	b.If the value at letters[mid] is less than or equal to the target, update left to mid + 1.
	c.Otherwise, update right to mid - 1.
3. If left is equal to the length of letters, return letters[0] as the target is greater than all elements.
4. Otherwise, return letters[left] as the target is either present or should be inserted at index left.

