# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- Make a set to store the difference between the target and the each element of the vector.
- First check if the letter is in last of array it has no greater char so return letter[0];
- Now compare each element of vector to target only if greater than itself (diff must be of next char not previous);
- If char found in vector then return next to it.
- Otherwire set is in accending order its first element is always the **min difference** so thats the answer [difference between next and target is always the shortest];
- DONE!!
# Complexity
